geodemoTXT: Varieties and subdialects of the Omotic language Yemsa, often referred to in the literature as Janjero, are spoken in Ethiopia, ZZSouthern Nations, Nationalities, and Peoples’ region: Yem zone; Oromia region: northeast of Jimma zone, Fofa (main village); mixed in Oromo villages; Saja, Deedoo, Sak’a, Jimma. SouthwestZZ; approx 92,200 speakers.
